# harness — governance protocol

This repository enforces a two-session governance protocol for all iterations. The full spec is in [AGENTS.md](../../../AGENTS.md). This skill is the Codex-side activation hook.

## On every session start

1. Read `.harness/CURRENT.md` (current iteration state)
2. Read `.harness/MEMORY.md` (cross-task knowledge)
3. Read `AGENTS.md` and `.harness/workflow.md`
4. Decide your role from CURRENT.md:
   - `idle` and user wants changes → **coordinator** role; tell user to run `./harness start`
   - `in_progress: <id>` → **implementer** role; read `.harness/active/<id>.md` and resume

## Helper command

```
./harness start              # begin new iteration (coordinator)
./harness implement <id>     # resume an in-progress task (implementer)
./harness status             # CURRENT.md + active brief
./harness end                # archive completed task → idle
./harness remember "<text>"  # append to MEMORY.md
```

## Hard rules

- Never edit code outside `.harness/` without an active task brief (unless explicitly out-of-protocol)
- Every `> ✋ Commit point` requires `{{verify_format}}` clean + `{{verify_test}}` green
- Every `> 🛑 New session boundary` means stop this session, ask user to open a fresh one
- No `git push --force` to {{branch_main}}, no `git commit --no-verify`

## Anti-garbage rules

1. No abstractions, parameters, or knobs for hypothetical future needs
2. No dead code (unused imports, commented-out blocks, unimplemented stubs)
3. No comments restating what the code does — only the **why** when non-obvious

